Popular Gospel music act Cece Winans and Alicia Keys have grabbed another set of Grammys at the 64th edition of the Recording Academy award show. Alicia Keys won with her album, ‘Alicia’ in the Best Immersive Audio Album category while Winans packed three different awards in three different categories. The veteran Gospel act picked up the Best Gospel Performance/Song for her song,   Full list of winners at Grammy Awards 2022     Five Nigerian skitmakers into music     Nigerian Idol 7: Gerald fails to make top 9   “Never Lost,” Best Contemporary Christian Music Performance for “Believe For It” alongside Dwan Hill, Kyle Lee, and Mitch Wong, and Best Gospel Album for ‘Believe For It.’ Other big winners of the night include Jon Bastie, and Chick Corea. On the same night, four Nigerians nominated in the Best Global Music Album and Best Global Music Performance lost out to Angelique Kidjo and Arooj Aftab respectively.